  "title": "Backend Security Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Main Responsibilities:</p><p>        1.        Implement and maintain security-related </p><p>REST API</p><p> platforms (including PKI services, authentication services, signature services, mainly using Java).</p><p>        2.        Develop and maintain customized </p><p>encryption</p><p> libraries for all company services.</p><p>        3.        Deliver clear, testable, and high-quality code.</p><p>        4.        Continuously optimize the stability and performance of the underlying infrastructure.</p><p>        5.        Participate in system architecture evolution and support large-scale system expansion.</p><p>        6.        Collaborate with distributed teams across different time zones and contribute to </p><p>agile development</p><p> processes.</p><p>Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) include but are not limited to:</p><p>        •        Stability and security maintenance of the Secret Management System.</p><p>        •        </p><p>Functional</p><p> iteration and daily maintenance efficiency of OTA backend systems.</p><p>        •        Quality of secondary development and delivery for digital key services.</p><p>        •        Timeliness of project delivery and code quality.</p><p>        •        Cross-team communication effectiveness and responsiveness in technical support.</p>",
